# agent-status

`agent-status` is generic local agent status standard plus tiny stdlib-only reference CLI. It gives cheap local visibility into live agent runtime and optional current task state.

## Why local status layer exists

Remote protocols answer remote questions. Local operators still need fast answer to: what agents run here, what are they doing, and is snapshot stale.

## Relation to A2A

This project is A2A-compatible local status layer. It complements A2A. It does not replace Agent Card discovery, Task APIs, or full A2A service behavior.

See:
- `docs/agent-status-v1alpha1.md`
- `docs/a2a-compat.md`

## Install

Python 3.10+.

Manual setup:

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
. .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
```

Devbox alternative:

```bash
devbox shell
python -m pip install -e .
```

Devbox uses same `.venv` path via `VENV_DIR=.venv`.

## Quick start

Emit one snapshot:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status emit \
  --agent-id pi-12345 \
  --agent-name pi \
  --lifecycle running \
  --workspace "$PWD" \
  --pid $$ \
  --task-id task-123 \
  --task-state working \
  --task-summary "refactor scheduler tests" \
  --task-status-timestamp 2026-06-20T16:44:55Z
```

List snapshots:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status list
```

Get one snapshot:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status get pi-12345
```

Watch snapshots:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status watch --interval 2
```

Validate file:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status validate examples/sample-status.json
```

## Protocol summary

Default status dir:

```text
${AGENT_STATUS_DIR:-${XDG_STATE_HOME:-~/.local/state}/agent-status}
```

One running agent instance = one file:

```text
<agent_id>.json
```

Core required fields:
- `schema_version`
- `agent_id`
- `agent_name`
- `runtime.lifecycle`
- `runtime.updated_at`

Task state uses A2A-style values. `idle`, `stale`, and `missing` are reader-derived only.

## JSON example

```json
{
  "schema_version": "agent-status/v1alpha1",
  "agent_id": "pi-12345",
  "agent_name": "pi",
  "runtime": {
    "lifecycle": "running",
    "updated_at": "2026-06-20T16:45:00Z",
    "last_activity_at": "2026-06-20T16:44:52Z",
    "pid": 12345,
    "workspace": "/home/julien/src/project"
  },
  "task": {
    "id": "task-123",
    "context_id": "ctx-456",
    "state": "working",
    "summary": "refactor scheduler tests",
    "status_timestamp": "2026-06-20T16:44:55Z"
  }
}
```

## CLI examples

Entry point after install:

```bash
agent-status emit --agent-id pi-1 --agent-name pi --lifecycle running
agent-status list
agent-status get pi-1
agent-status watch
agent-status validate examples/sample-status.json
```

## Writer rules

- atomic whole-file write
- absolute workspace path when known
- update on lifecycle, task, summary, heartbeat
- heartbeat every 15 to 30 seconds
- on clean exit: remove file or persist `runtime.lifecycle=stopped`

## Stale semantics

Default `stale_after` is 60 seconds.

Reader marks record stale when:

```text
now - runtime.updated_at > stale_after
```

If `runtime.lifecycle=running` and no `task`, reader may render `idle`.

## Validation

Run tests:

```bash
python3 -m unittest
```

Validate examples:

```bash
python3 -m agent_status validate examples/sample-status.json
python3 -m agent_status validate examples/a2a-linked-status.json
```

